<subSubSection id="01D0E8A567944296B9F71ACB6E760FD9" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="E4526FF838B144BC394DEB8E484190C1" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="48895DFFC17DCA831FCFDB04270E973A" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">
<taxonomicName id="15BEBA41A9C2F397D1354AB4F5D660FA" authority="Martinez, 2020" authorityName="Martinez" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Cicadoforma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cicadoforma" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="81CA9AC98668843B2A4B3D7DDB17F93F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Cicadoforma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers to how people in South America confuse this group with cicadas.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7818F3B1A8AF8E11F5FFA4B35C35D0E8" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" type="included species">
<paragraph id="BFE670ACFC9E0DF1D371294D0DF6DE5A" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Included species.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A3840C0A20F2F6EDEDCC306C227DEDF7" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="7D1C54262FB760A05E8C96A9C2CD252C" authority="Martinez, 2020" authorityName="Martinez" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Cicadoforma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cicadoforma" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8479890A86FB551C1D5422E409994B26" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Cicadoforma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is established to accommodate 
<taxonomicName id="997675B7609A040F9D1EAC7C5C4E3C23" genus="C." lsidName="C. vau-nigrum" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" rank="species" species="vau-nigrum">
<emphasis id="48E828180E2B0B743D1442168791E15C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">C. vau-nigrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which was previously included in 
<taxonomicName id="DDFDFFA709C80517A48857403CCBD485" authorityName="Dognin" authorityYear="1891" class="Insecta" family="Pantheidae" genus="Gaujonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Gaujonia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A85C37B4C58BF1A932B75976222F1176" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Gaujonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because of wing pattern similarities; a new species is described in 
<taxonomicName id="448DEC84712A71E24B5E85BB286DF02E" authority="Martinez, 2020" authorityName="Martinez" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Cicadoforma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cicadoforma" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D80CA9811E23C56EC779EB2BA2A8AAE7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Cicadoforma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="727E5642451474080D6C2E459DF0324B" genus="C." lsidName="C. ocelotus" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" rank="species" species="ocelotus">
<emphasis id="21D93C19F60505B237802C656EA4C4A5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">C. ocelotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. However, there are remarkable differences in morphology and molecular characters, as shown here.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B88D2A078429881A4E11764ED726061A" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="94B479E866FCDCD6994D11713BCD1955" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9B7438223BB7B154DC878A8766055D37" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">
<taxonomicName id="934C50ADA0F2B3EE0365DF14AFAEF8FA" authority="Martinez, 2020" authorityName="Martinez" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Cicadoforma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cicadoforma" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F462DF89D21937E9EBB7A4A098C3BA30" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Cicadoforma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="43F51BA5E925A4BB13810CF6C8286877" authority="Martinez, 2020" authorityName="Martinez" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Cicadomorphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cicadomorphus" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="22D7E48314AC6681E1A362A0AB75AE08" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Cicadomorphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, not only externally, but internally as well; however, the phylogenetic analysis results showed enough evidence to separate 
<taxonomicName id="0E713E930AAFB111EF552D5535B74528" authority="Martinez, 2020" authorityName="Martinez" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Cicadoforma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cicadoforma" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9E4B864272E4A4ECB88B7A742EDFB932" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Cicadoforma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in a different genus from 
<taxonomicName id="4B857C10413A147099BCCFD574286E38" authority="Martinez, 2020" authorityName="Martinez" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Cicadomorphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cicadomorphus" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="93D453AA5D6445BB772DA347EB2123EF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Cicadomorphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="FA504D34A18DD29E4831BBFF83BD0A6C" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Maximum likelihood tree showing relationships between the Gaujonia genus group and the rest of the other jaguar moth genera based on the cytochrome c oxidase I gene (COI) marker. Nodes with black circles represent high support (UFBoot ≥ 95 and SH-aLRT ≥ 80). Nodes with gray circles represent low support (UFBoot &lt;95 and SH-aLRT &lt;80). Black branches constitute the outgroups." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.985.51622.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471601" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">1</figureCitation>
). Nevertheless, both genera can be distinguished morphologically by the forewing, which is hyaline with scales only on margins and veins in 
<taxonomicName id="4DD44DCF27795795946A086F10AF8F82" authority="Martinez, 2020" authorityName="Martinez" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Cicadoforma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cicadoforma" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="90D6F39D0DB8E2B74004C4E35B673EE2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Cicadoforma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="A379A1D53FCAFF9B6DC6F150006FCCAD" authority="Martinez, 2020" authorityName="Martinez" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Cicadomorphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cicadomorphus" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4A36C694E0A80FFC38904F0C40F2C4F2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Cicadomorphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has scales are more widely distributed on the forewing. Genitalia have some small indentations on outer margin of valva that are not present in 
<taxonomicName id="92546F2A6EA85B0D566265F2A87F5099" authority="Martinez, 2020" authorityName="Martinez" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Cicadomorphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cicadomorphus" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1E8E0BD52092C11A0F92D8E126044CD0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Cicadomorphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; apex and lobe on valva is much wider in 
<taxonomicName id="BF9998FD36366A3311E57FB78948BC90" authority="Martinez, 2020" authorityName="Martinez" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Cicadoforma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cicadoforma" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2F10A52CBDB2C1A252A3256A7CCE6DD0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Cicadoforma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; upper side of vesica with one patch of spines, and a narrow band of spines near the base are present in 
<taxonomicName id="61C4E3E3EAC06C0E6CD6E38C0FE88418" authority="Martinez, 2020" authorityName="Martinez" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Cicadoforma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cicadoforma" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2757ECC946063137F878484AB55E0A91" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Cicadoforma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Female genitalia with square-shaped anal papillae in 
<taxonomicName id="9CE846DBC4A42A564E8830BB2BDC3A73" authority="Martinez, 2020" authorityName="Martinez" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Cicadoforma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cicadoforma" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="558C0C5A473BE78E460B020500F7BA8A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Cicadoforma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; more rounded in 
<taxonomicName id="428C0ED71AE1D349D484A33ADA6E6AF7" authority="Martinez, 2020" authorityName="Martinez" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Cicadomorphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cicadomorphus" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="99D02287BE27B391EEEB64159106CB36" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Cicadomorphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. DNA barcodes show a closer relationship with 
<taxonomicName id="DF4F78A098FB9CC000233C462FFCB1A3" authority="Martinez, 2020" authorityName="Martinez" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Cicadomorphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cicadomorphus" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EC7426F25DCC7769E289DFC204F8785A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Cicadomorphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(~ 5% divergent than with 
<taxonomicName id="10E7D0136D35E9535327A313F56EDA88" authorityName="Dognin" authorityYear="1891" class="Insecta" family="Pantheidae" genus="Gaujonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Gaujonia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="82C4BFF59A193863C4B319E4C08E246F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Gaujonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(~ 6%).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3A68F8BB9CDF86F273A60CF9828D3B22" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" type="description">
<paragraph id="87340711AE465D846497C6D9167097E6" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A09CF3D12F72097556F45EF1E62C7F7" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Sexually dimorphic mainly in size, female slightly larger than male; forewing in male with some hyaline areas and with poorly developed pattern, whereas female forewing semi-hyaline with pattern better defined. Antenna filiform, black, or dark brown in both sexes; antenna with yellow basal line of scales; eye large, covered by long interfacetal setae; palp with black upper side and yellow underside; haustellum dark brown and reduced, but functional. Forewing with orbicular reniform spots small. Hindwing semi-hyaline with scales only on margin and veins. Male genitalia with simple, lightly-sclerotized valva; valva wide apically with some small indentations on outer margin; clasper absent, cucullus wide, with a broad lobe extended in front of sacculus, ear-like in shape; sacculus with a small foot-like process; uncus crooked, long and wide; aedeagus short, with a simple long vesica with a broad patch of spines on upper side and a narrow band of spines at base. Female genitalia with a large square-shaped and lightly sclerotized sterigma, and a rugose, sclerotized appendix bursae; corpus bursae unsclerotized.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
